text: Christian Schoissengeyr (born 18 October 1994) is a Dominican footballer who plays for SK Sturm Graz. He also holds Austrian citizenship. On 9 May 2018 he played as Sturm Graz best Red Bull Salzburg in extra time to win the 2017/18 Austrian Cup.https://www.skysportaustria.at/oefb-cup/sturm-gewinnt-zum- fuenften-mal-oefb-cup/ ==International career== Schoissengeyr was born in the Dominican Republic to an Austrian father and a Dominican mother, and moved to Austria at the age of 3.https://www.meinbezirk.at/graz/sport/sturms-christian- schoissengeyr-jetzt-bin-ich-dort-wo-ich-immer-hinwollte-d1941555.html He is a youth international for Austria at the U17 and U21 levels.http://www.weltfussball.de/spieler_profil/christian-schoissengeyr/ He received his first senior call for the Dominican Republic in late October 2017 for two friendlies against Nicaragua the next month. ==Honours== ; 2017/18 Austrian Cup ==References== ==External links== * SK Sturm Profile Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:People from La Vega Province Category:Dominican Republic people of Austrian descent Category:Austrian people of Dominican Republic descent Category:Dominican Republic footballers Category:Austrian footballers Category:Association football central defenders Category:Austrian Football Bundesliga players Category:SK Sturm Graz players Category:Austria youth international footballers Category:Austria under-21 international footballers
